    <id>http://deshipu.art/projects/project-8643/</id>
    <title>Micro:Bob</title>
    <updated>2015-12-02T00:00:00+01:00</updated>
    <content type="html">&lt;section id="micro-bob"&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A simple bipedal robot controlled by Micro:Bit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="project-thumb"&gt;
&lt;a class="reference external image-reference" href="/_images/7581181449082984544.jpg"&gt;&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/7581181449082984544.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/7581181449082984544.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class="reference external image-reference" href="/_images/1219741466689791070.jpg"&gt;&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/1219741466689791070.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/1219741466689791070.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;iframe style="width: 500px; height: 281px;" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/khRb_HOsX6c"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
&lt;section id="logs"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Logs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul class="postlist-style-none postlist simple"&gt;
&lt;li class="ablog-post"&gt;&lt;p class="ablog-post-title"&gt;2016-07-25 - &lt;a class="reference internal" href="../../../projects/project-8643/log-42541/"&gt;Improved Knees&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="ablog-post"&gt;&lt;p class="ablog-post-title"&gt;2016-07-10 - &lt;a class="reference internal" href="../../../projects/project-8643/log-41610/"&gt;Connections and Exploding&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="ablog-post"&gt;&lt;p class="ablog-post-title"&gt;2016-06-25 - &lt;a class="reference internal" href="../../../projects/project-8643/log-40626/"&gt;Stability Problems Resolved&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="ablog-post"&gt;&lt;p class="ablog-post-title"&gt;2016-06-25 - &lt;a class="reference internal" href="../../../projects/project-8643/log-40634/"&gt;Mk II Walking&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="ablog-post"&gt;&lt;p class="ablog-post-title"&gt;2016-06-23 - &lt;a class="reference internal" href="../../../projects/project-8643/log-40494/"&gt;Micro:Bob MK II&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
&lt;section id="instructions"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Instructions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assembled robot.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/4988011466689915730.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/4988011466689915730.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;hr class="docutils" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I found a smaller plastic box for the head. Glued some LEDs, added
resistors and connected it all to the power switch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/7826501466688815903.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/7826501466688815903.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For now the head is taped with scotch tape. The hands are made from
coiled decoration wire, glued to the sides.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/6832841466688868826.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/6832841466688868826.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hands are cut out of the foamed plastic and glued at the ends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/8886141466689884942.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/8886141466689884942.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;hr class="docutils" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prepare the wires.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/1003851466679637691.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/1003851466679637691.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Connect them to the bolts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/6889121466679659715.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/6889121466679659715.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And then connect them to the servos. Power goes to the red/orange
wires, ground to the black/brown/blue wires, signal to the
white/yellow/green ones. The feet servos are connected together to the
first bolt.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/8347351466679753487.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/8347351466679753487.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;hr class="docutils" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Find the center of the box for the switch and drill a hole.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/158611466679782205.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/158611466679782205.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enlarge the hole and mount the switch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/6544031466679812369.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/6544031466679812369.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;hr class="docutils" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First you need to find a box for the body. Those plastic blocks with
pictures for children are pretty good – they are 5x5x5cm, made out of
pretty soft plastic which is easy to cut, and you can buy them in six-
packs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/256191466675392445.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/256191466675392445.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Of course you need to peel off and wash away the paper pictures from
them (unless you don’t mind your robot having them).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr class="docutils" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need to mark the holes for the servos. I align them so that the hub
of the servo is on the center line.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/4656271466675476691.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/4656271466675476691.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then I cut it with a knife, a metal saw or a dremel tool.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/8878881466675525803.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/8878881466675525803.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then drill the holes for screws.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/9990201466675874661.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/9990201466675874661.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;hr class="docutils" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We also need the holes for bolting on the Micro:bit.\&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/8217461466675562045.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/8217461466675562045.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once I mark the holes, I drill them with a small drill bit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/3644571466675600916.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/3644571466675600916.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And then I enlarge the holes with a screw or a dremel tool.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/2524031466675639097.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/2524031466675639097.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Finally I clean any irregularities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/7797531466675668736.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/7797531466675668736.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;hr class="docutils" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When I added the bolts and checked how the micro:bit fits, I
discovered that the battery plug is too thick.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/4761651466675710784.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/4761651466675710784.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So I quickly made an additional hole in the box.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/4938621466675771373.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/4938621466675771373.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now it fits perfectly, and also the servos can be attached.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/8539331466675804095.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/8539331466675804095.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;hr class="docutils" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I used some tiny screws and small pieces of foamed plastic to make the
knees out of the servo horns. Glue was applied liberally to make it
rigid.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/3941481466675921946.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/3941481466675921946.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some more glue to attach the feet. I used old PCBs from some project,
but pieces of plastic or wood, or even old credit cards could be used.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/6062291466676031350.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/6062291466676031350.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Finally, I cut some additional holes for the servo cables.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img alt="projects/project-8643/images/8104571466676057877.jpg" src="projects/project-8643/images/8104571466676057877.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
&lt;hr class="docutils" /&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
</content>
